  "text": "There are several possibilities to measure the cost of a solution. Here, we deal with makespan minimization for which the objective function is defined as follows. Every operation has a well-defined earliest starting time with respect to a solution . We assume that the operations being the first ones to be processed on their machine, as well as in their job, have an earliest starting time of 0. The earliest completion time of an operation with respect to a solution is denoted by and defined as . Then, given a solution , the objective function value (also called the makespan) is defined as [CITATION_1] The objective is to find a solution with minimum makespan.",
